==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overly
<hw>O"ver*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Careless; negligent;
inattentive; superficial; not thorough.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessive; too much.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: overly
<hw>o"ver*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an overly
manner.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overlying</ent>⟦br⟧
